            <!-- How To Use Drop-down -->
            <li class="dropdown"><a href="#" data-toggle="dropdown" class="dropdown-toggle">How to Use<b class="caret"></b></a>
              <ul class="dropdown-menu">
                <li>
                  <div class="yamm-content">
                    <div class="row">
                      <div id="accordion" class="panel-group">
                        <div class="panel panel-default">
                          <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">Searching the Museum</a></h4>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
                            <div class="panel-body">To use the search tool, simply enter keywords of your choice into the search box provided on the left of the screen. If you cannot see the search box, or wish to hide it, simply click the arrow button at the top left of the screen. Results from your search will be displayed in both a list under the search box, and via pins on the map. </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default">
                          <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">Navigating the Maps</a></h4>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">Navigating the maps on a desktop or laptop can be done using either a mouse or trackpad. Using either a mouse or trackpad, the maps can be moved around by using a click and drag in the appropriate direction. Zooming in and out on the maps using a mouse is done simply by scrolling the mouse wheel, whereas this task can be done on a trackpad by utilizing the trackpads pinch functionality. In addition to this, zooming can be achieved by clicking the buttons at the bottom right of the screen. Clicking on pins or rooms for further information is done by simply clicking the mouse or tapping the trackpad.</div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default">
                          <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">Navigating the Maps on Mobile</a></h4>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">Navigating the maps can also easily be achieved using a mobile or tablet device. The maps themselves can be moved by implementing a swipe or drag motion with your finger. Zooming in and out will require a pinching motion in order to enlarge or condense the map size, or simply clicking the button at the bottom left of the screen. Further information about pins or rooms can be found by tapping the screen with your finger.</div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default">
                          <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">Extra Features</a></h4>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">Locations of key places in the museum such as Toilets, Lifts, and the Information Desk can be found by clicking the respective buttons on the right hand side of the screen. The current map shown can be changed by selecting a floor using the drop down list at the top right of the screen. A full screen mode is available on desktops and laptops by clicking the ‘enlarge’ button found at the the top right, next to the floor selection list.</div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </li>
